title: For Sale:  F Class Vickers C and R transferable machine gun
postcontent: The F class Vickers is one of a small number of standard Vickers guns modified by Vickers to feed from a Lewis drum rather than belts. This gun was made by Vickers in England and sold to Japan as part of the 130 gun contract in the 1930's. It is one of only TWO known surviving examples on the ATF registry. This very gun is pictured in the Grand Old Lady of No Man's Land by Dolf L Goldsmith !! The buyer of this gun can rest well assured this will be a lucrative investment for years to come due to its rarity.
